# .dockerignore - trim build-context bloat (refs #499).
#
# The only build whose context is the repo root (`docker build ... .`)
# is dockerfile/Dockerfile.test-tools, and it copies NOTHING from the
# context (every COPY is `COPY --from=<stage>`). Dockerfile.example is
# only ever built against a synthesized consumer repo (integration-e2e
# job copies the template into a temp repo's .base/ and builds there),
# never against base's own root. So nothing the root-context build
# needs is excluded below.
#
# We still KEEP the source/template trees (script/, test/, config/,
# .base/, dockerfile/, Dockerfile, .hadolint.yaml, entrypoints) so this
# stays forward-safe: Dockerfile.example's lint/smoke stages COPY those
# paths, and the file doubles as the downstream template.

# ── VCS / repo metadata ──────────────────────────────────────────────
.git
.gitignore

# ── Docs (no build COPYs them) ───────────────────────────────────────
doc/
README*
LICENSE

# ── CI / lint config not consumed by any root-context build ──────────
.github/
.codecov.yaml

# ── Derived / generated artifacts (see script/docker/lib/gitignore.sh
#    _canonical_gitignore_entries) ──────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.bak
runtime.env
compose.yaml
setup.conf.bak
setup.conf.local
coverage/
.Dockerfile.generated
.docker.xauth

# ── Editor / OS / backup cruft ───────────────────────────────────────
*.bak
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/

# ── Local Claude Code session state ──────────────────────────────────
.claude
CLAUDE.md
